Google Jamboard is winding down
Jamboard application end of life information
The Jamboard application reached its end of life on December 31, 2024 across Web, iOS, Android and Google Meet devices.
Timeline for the Jamboard wind down
Milestone
Definition
Until October 1, 2024
Your Jamboard device and application functioned normally.
Starting on October 1, 2024
The Jamboard app went into view-only mode. You're no longer able to create new or edit existing jams on any platform, including the web, iPhone, iPad, Android, and Jamboard devices.
The
55-inch Jamboard device
reached its end of life. You're no longer able to use the device to join Google Meet meetings, and it won't save information to the cloud.
After December 31, 2024
You're no longer able to access the Jamboard app.
Jams will be converted to PDFs in Q1 2025.
Jams will be deleted after PDF conversion is complete.
What can I use moving forward?
Learn more about integrations with industry-leading third-party whiteboard tools such as,
FigJam
,
Lucidspark
, and
Miro
as alternatives for whiteboarding in Google Workspace. These popular tools have numerous advanced features that empower people to collaborate seamlessly together inside of Google Workspace.
What happened to my jams?
We recommend that you take proactive action to
export your jams
to PDF from Google Drive before we delete jams. We're attempting to convert your jams into PDF documents, which you will be able to find in your Drive.
This conversion process was designed to capture the visual elements of your jams as accurately as possible. However, due to the inherent differences between jams and PDFs, some content may not have translated perfectly.
Your jam files will be deleted over the following weeks after we have finished the conversion process in Q1 2025.
What if one of my jams was not converted to a PDF?
We're working hard to create a PDF of every jam. If you don't see a PDF for a specific jam yet, it means our system hasn't gotten to it yet. We have a lot of jams to process, so it will take some time to convert them all to PDFs.
We recommend that you take proactive action to
export your jams
to PDF from Drive before we delete jams.
Why is my PDF blank?
Sometimes the contents of a jam file may be corrupted, which prevents us from creating a PDF. In these cases, a blank PDF will be generated. The blank PDF serves as a record of the original jam file.
What if I own a Jamboard 55 device?
See
Jamboard device end of life information
.
What if I own a Series One Desk 27 and Board 65? Will there be another whiteboard app?
You can use third-party whiteboards on the Desk 27 and Board 65 using Google Meet add-ons. Your organization's administrator will need to install these add-ons. For details, see
Use add-ons with Google Meet on Desk 27 and Board 65
.
